cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper describes a data mining toolkit that incorporates a rich collection of data mining algorithms and allows auxiliary operations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Specifically, the focus on itemset extraction and association rule generation suggests a strong connection to machine learning and data mining, while the support for preparing and filtering data and interpreting extracted knowledge suggests a connection to databases and information retrieval.
